HEADWORD: bullpen
<hw>bull"pen`</hw> <pr>(b⟦usdot⟧l"p⟦ecr⟧n`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Baseball)</fld> <sn>1.</sn> <def>an open area in a baseball
stadium, off the playing field, where pitchers may warm up by throwing a
number of trial pitches before playing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <mark>[collective]</mark> <def>the relief pitchers on a
baseball team. Contrasted with <contr>starters</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bullpout</ent>⟦br⟧
